    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-11-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="99"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-11-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 407.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I confirm herewith telegrams<note n="a"
                        xml:id="d99fna">Printed, ante.</note> from and to you respecting the death
                    of Earl Li Hung-chang.</p>
                <p>The Government and people of the United States sympathize with China in the loss
                    sustained by her in the death of the statesman who for so many years shone
                    preeminent in the councils of his country, and who gave many proofs of his
                    esteem and friendship for the United States.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
